The paper deals with the study of sorting networks, which is a topic in computer science related to data structures and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the computation of new bounds on optimality, which is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of parallel sorting networks suggests the involvement of information theory (cs.IT) and neural networks (cs.NE).
